@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p class="text-muted">Last Updated: June 2026</p>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <strong>Internal Use Only:</strong> This application is a closed corporate system intended solely for authorized personnel of the organization.
</div>

<h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
<p>To manage employee records and operations efficiently, this system processes internal corporate data including, but not limited to:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Personal Identifiers:</strong> Full name, employee ID, email address, phone number, and physical address.</li>
    <li><strong>Employment Details:</strong> Department, designation, hire date, salary information, and shift schedules.</li>
    <li><strong>System Activity:</strong> User logins, timestamps, changes made to employee records, and system actions.</li>
</ul>

<h3>2. How We Use Data</h3>
<p>The collected information is used strictly to support organizational HR functions, including:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Maintaining up-to-date and accurate internal company records.</li>
    <li>Processing payroll, managing leave requests, and tracking attendance.</li>
    <li>Securing the system through audit trails and preventing unauthorized access.</li>
</ul>

<h3>3. Data Security and Retention</h3>
<p>We are committed to keeping corporate and employee data secure:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> System access is strictly restricted through role-based permissions (e.g., Admin, HR, Employee).</li>
    <li><strong>Data Security:</strong> All data transmissions are encrypted using standard protocol secure communication frameworks.</li>
    <li><strong>Retention:</strong> Employee data is securely retained in our internal database for the duration of employment and as required by local corporate policies.</li>
</ul>

<h3>4. Data Sharing</h3>
<p>Information stored in this system is strictly confidential. It is never sold, traded, or shared with external third parties, except where required by law or official government regulations (such as tax compliance).</p>

<h3>5. Contact Information</h3>
<p>For inquiries regarding data access permissions, corrections, or general system security, please reach out directly to the internal <strong>Human Resources (HR) Department</strong> or the <strong>IT Support Team</strong>.</p>
